Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.98,0:05:24.88,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like you to be late, Colonel Io.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.14,0:05:28.31,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Nike perished in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.31,0:05:29.52,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.20,0:05:34.81,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,General, the wind is delaying the reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.81,0:05:39.34,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,No matter. They weren't a part of our strategy to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.34,0:05:43.18,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,The battle will be long over by the time they get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.76,0:05:47.22,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,We'll capture Binonten and open the gates for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.82,0:05:48.94,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.66,0:05:55.54,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that one of Valkyrie squadron's soldiers, \NCleo, has been held prisoner there for some time. {name check}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.54,0:05:57.55,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,The Zaubraff's daughter, to be exact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.55,0:05:59.89,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,The report hasn't been verified yet, however.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.89,0:06:01.60,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.60,0:06:03.21,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,If the intel's correct, I'll rescue her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.21,0:06:08.72,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to topple the castle, and force Binonten to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.29,0:06:16.49,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Rescuing the princess would be the icing on the cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.49,0:06:19.26,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I've neither the right nor reason to stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.26,0:06:19.73,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.88,0:06:24.80,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,We shall now move on Binonten.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.80,0:06:26.99,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,All units, prepare for battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.14,0:06:38.16,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Let us meet again in Castle Binonten.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.16,0:06:39.12,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.69,0:06:49.80,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.72,0:07:18.93,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.05,0:07:21.04,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.33,0:07:29.78,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,What about Narvi and the guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.50,0:07:32.00,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.35,0:07:36.80,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,We noticed them after we found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.80,0:07:38.82,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy battalion is on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.82,0:07:40.89,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,They number 90 units.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.89,0:07:43.72,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse is planning to advance under the cover of darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.45,0:07:47.33,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,We can't afford to rest here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.33,0:07:48.40,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Can you handle it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,{following 2 lines simultaneous}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:49.78,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:49.78,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,No problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.78,0:07:51.84,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Everyone move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.84,0:07:52.75,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.37,0:07:58.48,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Come on Rygart,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.01,0:08:01.06,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.20,0:08:04.87,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.00,0:08:08.11,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Loggin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.11,0:08:08.85,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Loggin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.84,0:08:10.20,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Loggin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.20,0:08:11.52,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Loggin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.15,0:08:15.47,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,You're alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.81,0:08:19.32,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Narvi? What's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.32,0:08:21.14,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Your uniform's in tatters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.50,0:08:27.14,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Nile!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.14,0:08:28.64,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,You're not his ghost, are you? {alt; you're the real thing, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.48,0:08:34.50,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. Strange as it may seem, I'm still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.87,0:08:42.15,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,So what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.15,0:08:45.17,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Athens' battalion is heading for Binonten.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.17,0:08:47.29,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,We've got to circle around somehow and rejoin our forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.60,0:08:52.54,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow? You're telling me to floor this battered golem through total darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.54,0:08:54.47,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,What if the enemy sees us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.47,0:08:57.24,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Then we can score some ammo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.22,0:08:58.34,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.34,0:09:00.73,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,We just have to catch them off guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.25,0:09:05.05,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess this thing isn't exactly in fighting condition...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.91,0:09:17.58,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,The materials have arrived! Send a report to Queen Sigyn!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.58,0:09:19.70,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Request more ships for the evacuees!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.70,0:09:21.55,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that a little more important? {check}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.95,0:09:27.04,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,The quartz I've ordered is much sturdier than anything you might find in Krisna.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.55,0:09:31.25,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Please be careful, or else you'll break the machines. {lit; polisher/grinder}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.25,0:09:32.09,Default,Tec,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.09,0:09:34.69,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Also, be sure to complete it posthaste.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.69,0:09:35.29,Default,Tec,0000,0000,0000,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.47,0:09:45.18,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do, Gram?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.92,0:09:54.30,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,How is Rygart?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.30,0:09:58.51,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Word has it he's rendezvoused with General Baldr, and they're on their way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.51,0:10:00.05,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Good. And Narvi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.05,0:10:02.31,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't heard anything yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.31,0:10:09.13,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}We're able to house the remaining 20 percent of the city's \Nevacuees, but factoring in the northern villagers...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.13,0:10:11.24,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,We've been able to secure several vessels.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.24,0:10:13.47,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,What about our food and water reserves?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.47,0:10:15.21,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,At most, we have two month's worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.54,0:10:20.05,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Very good. That will buy us some time to repel Orlando.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.05,0:10:21.15,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Are you mad!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.83,0:10:26.08,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,General Borcuse is leading a whole battalion here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.08,0:10:29.31,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,He'll likely arrive tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.31,0:10:33.91,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,We have a mere 60 golems to defend ourselves—if he manages to breach our walls then—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.91,0:10:35.40,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Enough, Commander Konoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.65,0:10:40.20,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,I am well aware of our situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.59,0:10:51.21,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Can we triumph over fate? {alt; incredible odds}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.37,0:11:17.57,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,We stand little chance of beating Borcuse to the capital!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.57,0:11:20.00,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,We'll likely have to engage them without resupplying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.00,0:11:21.52,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.27,0:11:28.46,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart! We may encounter the enemy before the Delphine comes back online.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.78,0:11:31.88,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.88,0:11:34.42,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha. Just drop me off somewhere if we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.93,0:11:39.49,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I'll find a rock to crawl under.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.54,0:11:42.53,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.13,0:12:28.52,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,You're a godsend.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.52,0:12:32.25,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought we'd be able to find such a large piece of quartz.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.25,0:12:34.17,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,No trouble at all, milady.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.17,0:12:38.65,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,Though I fear the grinders may not be able to handle the stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.65,0:12:42.28,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not trying to tell you what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.28,0:12:46.78,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,The end result is up to you, but I know of a cheaper, more efficient way to get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.62,0:12:50.18,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention it'll save us some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.18,0:12:51.87,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about this? {reword?}{Can we afford to change plans this late ==> are you sure about this?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.87,0:12:54.86,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,My ship is practically a mobile laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.86,0:12:56.29,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing I don't have!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.70,0:13:03.29,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.29,0:13:05.31,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Approximately 90 in number!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.55,0:13:08.27,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.27,0:13:10.31,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,He's marching right up to our front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.07,0:13:13.85,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,I guess General Baldr wasn't fast enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.85,0:13:14.73,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy forces spotted!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.28,0:13:18.21,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Establish the first line of defense! {establish?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.88,0:13:25.01,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy forces!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.01,0:13:26.90,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Establish the first line of defense! {establish?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.90,0:13:28.57,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Formation one!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.03,0:13:32.87,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Primary and secondary east gate teams in position!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.28,0:13:35.26,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Do not let them set foot in our city!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.26,0:13:35.87,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.52,0:13:37.87,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, they're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.81,0:13:51.01,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,New golems? Did they follow us here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.54,0:13:57.39,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Bardess, they've slammed their doors shut on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.39,0:13:59.69,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Let's knock and invite ourselves in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.69,0:14:01.70,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Understood, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.70,0:14:03.56,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,All squads take your positions!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.56,0:14:04.90,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.45,0:14:08.41,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen! Let us fight like beasts! {reword?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.08,0:14:26.27,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,They're dispersing! {timing check}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.28,0:14:28.26,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,27 moving west, 18 advancing eastward!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.54,0:14:31.28,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,So he insists on charging the front gate himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.46,0:14:37.39,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Open fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.04,0:14:52.50,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Your majesty, please seek shelter!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.50,0:14:53.49,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.06,0:14:55.61,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Have the townspeople all evacuated?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.61,0:14:56.89,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,And the refugees?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.89,0:15:00.21,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone that arrived up until now is safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.19,0:15:04.26,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Those who haven't have lost their chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.26,0:15:09.21,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,We had men searching the area, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.43,0:15:13.87,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.34,0:15:15.73,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Astonishing...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.27,0:15:18.19,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Let's begin work on the next phase!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.19,0:15:19.64,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Are the ligaments ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.65,0:15:55.76,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,They've got us right where they want us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.70,0:15:57.93,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Cover me! I'll open the gate! {timing check}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.60,0:16:12.78,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Leto?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.45,0:16:17.70,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,General Bardess' squad has rendezvoused with General Borcuse's forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.70,0:16:20.15,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,And sniping is my specialty, sir. {she's saying she doesn't need to help  Bardess' squad anymore}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.11,0:16:23.58,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent work!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.97,0:16:36.44,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,I was expecting a bigger welcome than this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.61,0:16:50.42,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.51,0:16:56.78,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Well, aren't we brave?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.30,0:17:04.79,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, men.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.55,0:17:10.10,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let them get inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.67,0:17:18.12,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Fall back to secondary positions!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.12,0:17:19.64,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let them break through the northern gates!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.90,0:17:35.70,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,There he is. Lady Siqwyn was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.16,0:17:38.08,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,That's good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.84,0:17:40.67,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Let's attach the ligaments.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.67,0:17:42.20,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Is the reinforced quartz ready yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.78,0:17:46.29,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,You want those giant ligaments to move?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.95,0:17:49.27,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,They can’t move like normal ones do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.33,0:17:53.75,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But we need something with the strength and flexibility to handle its large mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.56,0:17:57.05,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,What about the joint ligaments?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.87,0:18:00.74,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Wait right there, I'll go get them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.74,0:18:02.48,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Sigyn, please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.09,0:18:07.45,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Your accuracy is commendable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:23.45,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot let you advance any further!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.35,0:18:32.29,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I never expected to get this far with such a small force to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.13,0:18:40.53,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we’re losing the race to the guys at the east gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.58,0:18:50.70,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Secure all roads leading to the north gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.70,0:18:51.57,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:56.05,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take out their sniper!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.30,0:18:58.78,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Leto!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.09,0:19:12.17,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,They've got tougher golems now? {reword?}{sounds good to me}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.06,0:19:33.61,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,General Baldr, I presume?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.61,0:19:36.32,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't expecting you to attack our rear flank. {redundant?}{probably but it can't be helped}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.05,0:19:40.44,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Each of you pick an opponent. Godspeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.44,0:19:41.45,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.20,0:20:03.45,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Sigyn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.45,0:20:05.28,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Just a moment, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.77,0:20:24.19,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Sit down on the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.19,0:20:24.82,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.82,0:20:25.57,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.57,0:20:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.24,0:20:31.43,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,You can come in now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.99,0:20:35.20,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Take this, and this. Quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.20,0:20:36.76,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,You two at the door, please help assist us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.76,0:20:38.71,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.71,0:20:40.32,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry. We don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.32,0:20:41.65,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.65,0:20:42.69,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,These too, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.66,0:20:45.12,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Be extremely careful with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.12,0:20:45.98,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.98,0:20:47.70,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.51,0:20:55.52,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,All clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.02,0:21:02.51,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I'm developing weaponry to fight off your nation's golems.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.24,0:21:04.22,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,...I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.22,0:21:07.35,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But only the Delphine can use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.10,0:21:10.30,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I'll present it to Rygart when he returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.14,0:21:14.25,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still awaiting news of his arrival, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.03,0:21:20.17,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But I know he'll come back. He swore he would.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.68,0:21:26.84,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stop being angry once you come home safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.10,0:21:34.13,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.25,0:21:43.53,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Cleo, I want you to promise me something as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.93,0:21:47.00,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.48,0:21:49.95,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Sigyn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.43,0:22:05.42,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for us to go, Del.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.93,0:23:18.24,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you think you're going?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.24,0:23:19.25,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.25,0:23:22.00,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.43,0:23:23.51,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Not like this! {reword?}{I won't stand for this => not like this -- which is appropriate given the scene}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.19,0:23:53.50,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Impressed, General Baldr.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.40,0:23:57.75,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,You've cleverly managed to buy some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.75,0:23:59.58,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,But it ends now!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.53,0:24:04.88,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but we'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.47,0:24:09.67,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,What went through your mind when you saw the villagers?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.28,0:24:12.43,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.43,0:24:14.89,Default,Zes,0000,0000,0000,,Krisna is as good as finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.89,0:24:16.66,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,You filthy barbarians!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.66,0:24:19.47,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,“That's war. There's nothing I could do?”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.47,0:24:22.15,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let the deaths of strangers weigh too heavily on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.15,0:24:23.81,Default,Gir,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.88,0:24:34.80,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Del.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.61,0:24:56.32,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,Tragic, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.32,0:24:59.60,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,The outcome is already decided, yet you must still fight to the death.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.87,0:25:27.76,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Use the buildings as cover and keep moving! {alt; advancing}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.76,0:25:28.88,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Double-time it to the rendezvous point!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.88,0:25:30.36,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel Io!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.36,0:25:32.38,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Leto, continue to cover our flank!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.71,0:25:37.02,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Now! Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.02,0:25:37.55,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.46,0:25:42.27,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stay here and cover you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.60,0:25:46.91,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,We made it here faster than anticipated. All of you can handle the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.91,0:25:48.27,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Cover me, Leto!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.60,0:25:49.70,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.95,0:25:55.29,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.20,0:26:03.40,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,You just don't get it, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.40,0:26:07.75,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,You've already failed to protect the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.60,0:26:13.74,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.57,0:26:45.54,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.45,0:26:52.41,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,If it isn't the Black Golem.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.41,0:26:55.51,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I've never once seen you fire a pressure gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.96,0:27:00.64,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.64,0:27:03.35,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a unique trait of your mysterious golem?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.28,0:27:07.06,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Or a lack of ability on the part of its pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.55,0:27:09.48,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Borcuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.48,0:27:13.21,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,But I think I'll wait until after I've taken the palace to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.83,0:27:19.95,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure not to leave any slack.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.95,0:27:21.90,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Sigyn, please stand back!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.90,0:27:22.28,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Tighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.01,0:27:23.95,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.95,0:27:26.93,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Sigyn, the Delphine has returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.93,0:27:28.15,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,How's its armor?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.15,0:27:31.24,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,Some was obtained and equipped while it was on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.24,0:27:35.31,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,He's currently engaged in combat on the central highway, moving towards our location.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.31,0:27:36.24,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.89,0:27:43.08,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Shit, the battle's already begun!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.08,0:27:44.40,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,What happened at the north gate?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.25,0:27:46.85,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,The Fabnirs are in pieces! {name check}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.85,0:27:48.53,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on tight!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.70,0:27:58.86,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I've no intention of fighting unarmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.86,0:28:00.03,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.53,0:28:07.38,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.38,0:28:11.25,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive movements as usual, Black Golem.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.93,0:28:13.21,Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,Not that it means anything, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.15,0:28:43.99,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}I've read countless times that in the olden days of warfare, \Nit often came down to people throwing stones at each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.89,0:28:48.16,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,But I never thought I'd be a part of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.96,0:28:59.57,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good. My arm's going to be destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.57,0:29:01.88,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I recall reading about this as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.88,0:29:04.67,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,A sort of hand-to-hand warfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.06,0:29:13.83,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Very good defense!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.83,0:29:16.40,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Not good enough to defend your whole nation though.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.73,0:29:21.18,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Let's begin the assembly!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.99,0:29:26.99,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Wind them up as tight as possible to ensure the ligament's strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.22,0:29:48.51,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,It seems I was mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.51,0:29:55.89,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}Indeed, the Black Golem's power, which my nation and \NI find so perplexing, does not owe itself to its pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.51,0:30:02.82,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,But in your own way, you are equally foreign to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.82,0:30:07.32,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,A relic of civilizations past reborn, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.83,0:30:09.15,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.15,0:30:11.83,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,There's no telling what other weapons he might be carrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.21,0:30:20.60,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Tertiary defense lines have been breached!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.60,0:30:22.36,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,We're fighting off forces coming from the west!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.36,0:30:25.21,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy squads from the east are advancing towards the city center!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.68,0:30:29.97,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,I have to get back to them! {her army, that is}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.97,0:30:35.59,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,We've lost too much time!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.59,0:30:38.39,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,We'll circle around and attack at the crossroads!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.39,0:30:40.81,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Time to let loose!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.37,0:30:43.47,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.07,0:30:44.75,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.75,0:30:47.06,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,The palace is glistening.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.97,0:30:50.58,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! We won't let them get near it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.89,0:31:08.01,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.51,0:31:15.82,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,You don't even understand how to fight! What's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.69,0:32:07.44,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable! How can something so heavy even move? {lit: was weight not a concern when they built this?}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.44,0:32:11.95,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,You little prick!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.48,0:32:18.70,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Was that what he was after?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.70,0:32:22.96,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,But why not take the pressure gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.96,0:32:25.96,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,He should be able to manipulate the quartz, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.30,0:32:33.49,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I had heard about people with no powers, {check-did we use a special word for them?}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.49,0:32:39.20,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,but I've never met one of the rare individuals before.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.70,0:32:44.31,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be... they weren't just a myth?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.00,0:32:47.63,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Rygart? The Delphine too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.63,0:32:50.21,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,He's currently engaged in combat near the crossroads.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.21,0:32:51.51,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.51,0:32:52.53,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,You mean this giant thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.35,0:32:57.49,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I know, it's rather primitive for a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.49,0:33:00.03,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,That's kind of an understatement.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.03,0:33:04.62,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But the truth is the pilot, Rygart Arrow, can't use magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.62,0:33:05.61,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.75,0:33:08.44,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,Then how does he fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.44,0:33:13.54,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,The Delphine was a product of the bygone \Ncivilization, and extremely difficult to maneuver.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.54,0:33:18.53,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,But for some reason, only the powerless Rygart, scorned for his lack of magic, can make it move.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.00,0:33:21.85,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,And we've yet to understand why.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.44,0:33:29.60,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,But despite that, he can still use this weapon somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.60,0:33:33.98,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I think, {delay}it's just because he's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.41,0:33:37.49,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,All preparations complete! What about the Delphine?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.11,0:33:39.44,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Open the gates!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.44,0:33:41.75,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,I will explain it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.16,0:33:46.50,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Sigyn!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.23,0:33:48.68,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's{\i0} the strange one?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.68,0:33:49.97,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone to the first inner gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.97,0:33:50.92,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get it to the gate asap!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.39,0:34:07.42,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,One born without the gift of magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.33,0:34:15.86,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Cleo Zaubraff of the Zess Squadron?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.25,0:34:19.47,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,I am Io, of the Borcuse Battalion.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.47,0:34:24.08,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm Cleo, of Zess—I mean, the Valkyrie squadron!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.08,0:34:24.83,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.83,0:34:27.02,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.02,0:34:28.84,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,I promise I'll get you back to Athens.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.42,0:34:30.83,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Just leave the rest to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.77,0:34:33.31,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.32,0:34:56.57,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Sigyn.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.18,0:35:01.55,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,That's the guy from before!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.55,0:35:03.24,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,I'll finish you off this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.44,0:35:09.54,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,There's no end to these bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.37,0:35:31.48,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but the ligament you just cut wasn't necessary anyway. {lit; idle, useless}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.08,0:35:33.89,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.60,0:35:42.73,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Sigyn?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.12,0:35:45.66,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.66,0:35:48.45,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Over there, Rygart! Take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.43,0:36:00.92,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see what you can do. {alt; show me what you've got}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.28,0:36:10.81,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,It's extremely dangerous here. Please fall back.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.81,0:36:14.94,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Are you mad!? You first, Lady Sigyn!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.94,0:36:17.65,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot return until you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.10,0:36:34.71,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,What a splendidly fitting weapon for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.25,0:36:37.57,Default,Rig,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.85,0:36:39.71,Default,Rig,0000,0000,0000,,You alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.71,0:36:40.61,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.30,0:36:42.59,Default,Rig,0000,0000,0000,,Want me to call for help?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.59,0:36:44.55,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,That won't be necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.55,0:36:48.40,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, kid, you need to find somewhere to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.40,0:36:50.15,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,The city's swarming with Athens' soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.15,0:36:51.01,Default,Rig,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.70,0:37:05.20,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, why won't he go down already!?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.33,0:37:13.43,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.38,0:37:19.49,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but this is as far as I can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.49,0:37:20.88,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Please escape on your own!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.30,0:37:25.13,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take care of this one, so you've got to survive at all costs!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.13,0:37:25.80,Default,Cle,0000,0000,0000,,But Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.80,0:37:26.91,Default,Io,0000,0000,0000,,Get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.93,0:37:35.61,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.15,0:37:42.65,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get so cocky!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.27,0:37:55.89,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Narvi!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.66,0:37:57.49,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Loggin!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.53,0:37:59.45,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,S'cuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.38,0:38:01.94,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Let me handle this, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.80,0:38:17.71,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, that's heavy!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.71,0:38:18.94,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Nile!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.94,0:38:21.86,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Don't just stand there! They're \Nattacking the secondary castle walls! {alt; ramparts}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.12,0:38:22.75,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.01,0:38:24.74,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Nile!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.25,0:38:27.20,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,I just had a score to settle with him, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.63,0:38:29.16,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,And trust me, we're even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.16,0:38:30.25,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,You're insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.25,0:38:31.15,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Loggin, behind you!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.79,0:38:35.84,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.96,0:38:39.65,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,We'll finish this next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.94,0:38:51.80,Default,Gua(x2),0000,0000,0000,,Lady Sigyn!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.80,0:38:53.20,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Please, let me down here!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.20,0:38:54.16,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,We can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.16,0:38:56.30,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,The Delphine needs our help!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.30,0:38:58.23,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,Closing the primary castle walls!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.19,0:39:36.95,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Still managed to hold onto it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.95,0:39:37.98,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Tenacious little bugger.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.35,0:39:49.46,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Just what are you made of, pal? {talking to the weapon, I believe}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.25,0:40:24.61,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.61,0:40:29.26,Default,Sci,0000,0000,0000,,Even the mighty Borcuse is caught off guard by your weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.19,0:40:32.32,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, King Hodr!?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.32,0:40:33.20,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Come back inside at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.18,0:40:36.76,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing? You could be shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.76,0:40:37.55,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Minister.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.55,0:40:37.91,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,Milord?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.59,0:40:42.80,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,That brainless idiot Rygart is fighting to the death.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.85,0:40:45.04,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of our nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.54,0:40:52.06,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,He's fighting an enemy general in a golem we know nothing about.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.06,0:40:53.86,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,And I ordered him to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.45,0:40:59.09,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not true. I asked him to.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.95,0:41:04.51,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,I gave him the option to refuse, yet he still took up arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.00,0:41:07.59,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,With his own hands, devoid of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.89,0:41:14.79,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to that, standing in the rain is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.79,0:41:16.58,Default,Min,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.88,0:41:33.65,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,I can see the limitations of your weapon. {alt; weaknesses}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.16,0:41:39.63,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,How can the ligaments be wound so tightly?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.02,0:42:05.00,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.33,0:42:06.85,Default,Gua(x3),0000,0000,0000,,Lady Sigyn!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.85,0:42:07.70,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Unhand me!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.70,0:42:08.64,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,You can't go out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.12,0:42:18.13,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself! Who {\i1}are{\i0} you!? {lit; where are you from}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.13,0:42:20.14,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see the kind of freak you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.99,0:43:01.93,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.99,0:43:24.32,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,The Black Golem...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.03,0:43:58.48,Default,Bor,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry Leda, Io will still come to your recital. {name check}{check- not 100% sure he says "Io" here}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.29,0:44:56.00,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,Just before mid-day, word of General Borcuse's death reached his battalion,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.00,0:44:59.30,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,and they made a temporary retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.30,0:45:05.30,Default,Bal,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't take long for the news to reach Secretary General Loquis. {name check}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.57,0:45:09.30,Default,Zes,0000,0000,0000,,Cleo's alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.30,0:45:11.50,Default,Gen,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. She's unharmed. {lit; alive/survived}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.50,0:45:15.90,Default,Gen,0000,0000,0000,,She was seen escaping Binonten onboard a trade vessel.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.90,0:45:17.30,Default,Zes,0000,0000,0000,,Where is she now?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.30,0:45:19.16,Default,Gen,0000,0000,0000,,Her whereabouts are currently unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.16,0:45:20.26,Default,Zes,0000,0000,0000,,I can't just leave her to fend for herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.37,0:45:24.13,Default,Zes,0000,0000,0000,,Let's form a search party immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.13,0:45:25.64,Default,Gen,0000,0000,0000,,But what about your leg?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.64,0:45:28.49,Default,Zes,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine. I'll go convince my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.49,0:45:30.15,Default,Zes,0000,0000,0000,,Are you coming with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.15,0:45:31.20,Default,Gen,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.73,0:45:33.08,Default,Wif,0000,0000,0000,,Dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.30,0:45:35.57,Default,Zes,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be gone long.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.60,0:45:44.54,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Narvi!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.12,0:45:49.68,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Why!? Why did General True have to die!?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.11,0:45:53.69,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Don't beat yourself up over it! \NThere's nothing we could've done!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.66,0:45:58.05,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,He's long gone, okay!?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.61,0:45:59.67,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Narvi.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.51,0:46:06.78,Default,Nil,0000,0000,0000,,Loggin.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.76,0:46:09.83,Default,Log,0000,0000,0000,,Tragic, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.85,0:46:19.76,Default,Gua,0000,0000,0000,,Can you stand?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.76,0:46:22.90,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm fine. Just a few scrapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.00,0:46:27.18,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.18,0:46:28.80,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,I came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.00,0:46:31.30,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Just like I promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.73,0:46:40.33,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,It's not over yet, though. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.32,0:46:42.32,Default,Hod,0000,0000,0000,,Rygart.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.75,0:46:47.31,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Zess will be back, won't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.76,0:47:00.33,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to fight each other again.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.70,0:47:03.84,Default,Rig,0000,0000,0000,,Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.79,0:47:06.86,Default,Rig,0000,0000,0000,,That was {\i1}you{\i0} riding that thing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.38,0:47:10.48,Default,Ryg,0000,0000,0000,,Regarz! You're alive! {regarz or rigarz?}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.73,0:47:12.66,Default,Rig,0000,0000,0000,,That's all you have to say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.66,0:47:16.47,Default,Rig,0000,0000,0000,,You never came back, so I went looking all over for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.48,0:47:21.08,Default,Rig,0000,0000,0000,,You said “I'm going to the capital”, and that was it!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.82,0:47:28.92,Default,Rig,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell have you been doing this whole time!?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.84,0:47:42.82,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}A lone flower sprung from the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.47,0:47:51.93,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}silently watches war unfold.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.93,0:48:00.05,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}It grieves in silence,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.48,0:48:09.07,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}asking, “why must they sacrifice others to protect what they hold dear?”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.07,0:48:26.87,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}“And what are they fighting for?”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.24,0:48:43.47,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}Let us believe that the future holds hope yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.47,0:48:52.05,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}that there is a deeper meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.05,0:49:13.39,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}in the trials we've faced to protect those we love.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.39,0:49:21.58,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}If only we could be like this forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.01,0:49:30.54,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}my beloved says, and laughs.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.54,0:49:39.08,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}Everybody longs for these peaceful days,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.08,0:49:48.04,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}yet my heart still grieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.75,0:50:12.00,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}I can almost hear their hearts breaking
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.29,0:50:22.29,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}as people lost all that was dear to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.64,0:50:30.23,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}And I wonder if I don't deserve the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.46,0:51:15.64,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}Let us believe that the future holds hope yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.64,0:51:24.24,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}that there is a deeper meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.24,0:51:48.34,Ending 2,son,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,3000)\be1}in the trials we've faced to protect those we love.
